cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a protocol innovation in the transport layer of the TCP/IP protocol stack. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper describes the implementation of the MPTCP congestion control algorithms in the Linux kernel. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as MPTCP has security implications and the paper may touch on those. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is a possibility as the paper discusses the architecture of the MPTCP protocol and its implementation in the Linux kernel. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as MPTCP involves multiple subflows and alternative paths, which could be seen as a form of distributed computing.
